t": false, "description": "Area: Trait system"}, {"id": 60329014, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2MDMyOTAxNA==", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/P-low", "name": "P-low", "color": "eb6420", "default": false, "description": "Low priority"}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 15, "created_at": "2013-04-21T22:16:58Z", "updated_at": "2015-03-08T08:02:03Z", "closed_at": "2014-10-13T22:07:21Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "This would be very useful for `core::num` (see #4819), and also mathematics libraries.\n\n``` rust\n// overloads `+=`\n#[lang=\"add_assign\"]\ntrait AddAssign<RHS> {\n    fn add_assign(&mut self, &other: RHS);\n}\n\n// overloads `-=`\n#[lang=\"sub_assign\"]\ntrait SubAssign<RHS> {\n    fn sub_assign(&mut self, &other: RHS);\n}\n\n// overloads `*=`\n#[lang=\"mul_assign\"]\ntrait MulAssign<RHS> {\n    fn mul_assign(&mut self, &other: RHS);\n}\n\n// overloads `/=`\n#[lang=\"quot_assign\"]\ntrait QuotAssign<RHS> {\n    fn quot_assign(&mut self, &other: RHS);\n}\n\n// overloads `%=`\n#[lang=\"rem_assign\"]\ntrait RemAssign<RHS> {\n    fn rem_assign(&mut self, &other: RHS);\n}\n```\n\nIt would also be useful to be able to assign to values accessed via the index operator. This would return a mutable reference to the element. =, +=, -=, *=, /=, and %= would then be based off the overloads defined for that element type.\n\n``` rust\n#[lang=\"index_assign\"]\ntrait IndexAssign<Index,Element> {\n    fn mut_index<'a>(&'a mut self, index: Index) -> &'a mut Element;\n}\n```\n\nEdit: Removed `Assign` trait for `=` operator.\n", "closed_by": {"login": "rust-highfive", "id": 7378925, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjczNzg5MjU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7378925?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/rust-highfive", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-highfive", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/us